    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters April 26th with a clear priority on leveraging speed and favorable matchups against suspect arms. **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (79.92) stands as our premier play today, benefiting from a massive 19% boost due to Arrighetti\u2019s favorable xERA and a generous 100% stolen base opportunity rating against the opposing battery. Close behind him, **James Wood** (73.18) and **Corbin Carroll** (71.54) anchor the outfield. **James Wood** receives a significant cushion from his leadoff spot, while **Corbin Carroll** continues to offer elite floor value despite a tougher matchup against King. We are also leaning on **Tyler Soderstrom** (65.85) in a high-leverage 3rd-hole spot, where his dynamic platoon advantage against Rocker makes him a superior choice over our peripheral bench pieces.\n\nOur bench strategy remains disciplined, with **Vinnie Pasquantino** (39.32) serving as the most difficult omission. Despite his talent, the combination of a tough matchup against Detmers and a -15% platoon penalty pushed his score just below our \"Zebras Floor\" of 40.0, forcing us to prioritize the higher-ceiling efficiency of **Jose Caballero** (56.31). **Jose Caballero** provides necessary utility; while he faces a -13% platoon drag, his matchup against Arrighetti combined with a high-probability SB environment keeps him viable. Conversely, **Austin Riley** (56.16) remains in the lineup despite a tough draw against Nola; his BvP historical edge (+8%) remains the primary reason he holds onto the 3B spot despite the presence of an elite arm and a quick catcher. \n\nRisk management for today centers on our catching tandem, as **Dalton Rushing** (46.97) and **Luis Campusano** (43.12) are both operating in the \"Marginal\" efficiency tier. **Dalton Rushing** faces a difficult task against Imanaga, and his platoon disadvantage as a left-handed bat against a lefty pitcher is partially mitigated only by favorable wind conditions. Owners should be wary of the potential for low-scoring outcomes from these slots. We continue to monitor the status of **Josh Naylor** and **Giancarlo Stanton**, who are currently unavailable, ensuring that our depth\u2014including **Max Muncy**, **Gabriel Moreno**, **Carson Williams**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Kyle Karros**, **Alex Freeland**, and **Travis Bazzana**\u2014remains ready should any late-day injury reports emerge from the league office.",
